Renowned artists have taken to streets around Cape Town to create colourful and creative artworks to drive the message around the benefits of vaccinating. eNCA's Tanya Nefdt reports. #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - The coronavirus pandemic is still very much part of our daily reality here in South Africa. Studies reveal that under 30 percent of the population is fully vaccinated. Now one organisation is partnering with non-profit body Baz–Art to raise awareness around the importance of vaccinating. They want to inspire behavioural change and debunk the myths. * eNCA's Tanya Nefdt reports.